AWS Account (Free Tier)

EC2 Ubuntu instance

Step-by-Step Deployment Guide (AWS + Ubuntu EC2

1Ô∏è‚É£ Create Your Simple Web App

Create a file index.html in your project folder:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My Cloud App</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Hello AWS Cloud!</h1>
  <p>This is my first web app hosted on an EC2 Ubuntu instance.</p>
</body>
</html>

2Ô∏è‚É£ Launch an EC2 Instance

Go to AWS Management Console ‚Üí EC2.

Click Launch Instance.

Name: my-web-app

AMI: Choose Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS.

Instance type: t2.micro (Free Tier)

Key pair: Create or select one (download .pem file).

Security group:

Allow HTTP (port 80) and SSH (port 22).

Click Launch Instance.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Connect to Your EC2 Instance

In your terminal (on your local machine):

chmod 400 your-key.pem
ssh -i your-key.pem ubuntu@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>

4Ô∏è‚É£ Install a Web Server (Apache or Nginx)

Let‚Äôs use Apache for simplicity:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install apache2 -y


Start and enable Apache:

sudo systemctl start apache2
sudo systemctl enable apache2


Check the status:

sudo systemctl status apache2

5Ô∏è‚É£ Deploy Your Web App

Upload your index.html file to the Apache web root:

sudo rm /var/www/html/index.html
sudo nano /var/www/html/index.html


Paste your HTML content here, then save (Ctrl + O, Enter, Ctrl + X).

Alternatively, you can copy files via SCP:

scp -i your-key.pem index.html ubuntu@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:/tmp
sudo mv /tmp/index.html /var/www/html/

6Ô∏è‚É£ Test Your App

Open your browser and visit:

http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>/


You should see your page live üéâ

7Ô∏è‚É£ (Optional) Use a Custom Domain

If you own a domain (e.g., from Freenom or Namecheap):

Go to your domain DNS settings.

Create an A Record pointing to your EC2 Public IP.

After propagation, your domain will show your app.

8Ô∏è‚É£ Take Required Screenshots

‚úÖ Deliverables:

Screenshot of:

Web app running in browser (showing public URL).

AWS EC2 console showing your instance running.

Source code (ZIP or GitHub repo link).

Short deployment note.

üßæ Example Deployment Note

Title: AWS EC2 Web App Deployment (Ubuntu + Apache)

Steps Summary:

Created index.html for my simple web app.

Launched AWS EC2 Ubuntu instance (t2.micro).

Installed Apache web server.

Uploaded and served HTML file at /var/www/html/.

App accessible publicly at http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>/.

Result:
Website successfully hosted on AWS using an Ubuntu EC2 instance.

üßπ 9Ô∏è‚É£ Clean Up Resources

When done, to avoid charges:

sudo systemctl stop apache2
exit


Then terminate the instance in AWS Console.
